FBIS4-30527 "dreas124_c_94012" FBIS-EAS-94-124 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 North Korea ROK Party Call for Dialogue in Strikes Cited ROK Party Call for Dialogue in Strikes Cited SK2806050694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0443 GMT 28 Jun 94 SK2806050694 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, June 28 (KCNA) -- The South Korean opposition Democratic Party at a general meeting of assemblymen on June 25 contended that the strike of the railway and subway workers was attributable to the anachronistic labour policy of the authorities and their ruthless invocation of "government" power, a Seoul-based radio report said. In a resolution it urged an immediate release of the workers whisked away and a halt to the invocation of "government" power against the strike. The resolution said the authorities must solve the problem through dialogue with railway and subway trade unions.
